==Gameplay==
''The Human Adventure'' is a game which follows miniaturized scientists traveling through a person's bloodstream to fight cancer.<ref name="SG"/> The game is controlled via single-word commands.<ref name=manual/>

==Reception==
Russ Williams reviewed ''The Human Adventure'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 47.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last= Williams |first= Russ  |date=January 1982 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=47|pages=32}}</ref> Williams commented that "This is basically a nifty little game based on a popular SF theme.  It has the added advantage of being educational.  I learned more about human anatomy from this game than I did in my biology class!"<ref name="SG"/>

